    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This high-revving powerplant utilizes individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system to deliver linear power up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a torque-sensing M-variable limited-slip differential. To ensure structural integrity, the rear subframe has been reinforced, and the suspension geometry is maintained by refreshed bushings. While the aesthetic reflects its status as a driven machine, the mechanical vitals remain sharp, with consistent compression across all cylinders and immediate throttle response. A driver-spec example optimized for chassis feedback and longitudinal grip.",
      "price": 31500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 42
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_3",
